  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="65b8-ace5-2b18-a299" name="Stormtroopers" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>A Unit may attempt a second Movement Order after succeeding in its first Movement Order. The second Movement Order must be different from the first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a4da-aea0-d957-477c" name="Third Reich" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Troops of the Third Reich have a better Last Stand rating.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d1c5-7b76-8261-8463" name="Tiger Ace" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Tiger Aces have a better Last Stand rating and a significantly better Remount rating.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="674b-e4fa-e2db-622a" name="Bazooka Skirts" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>A Tank Team with Bazooka Skirts increases its Side armour to 5 against weapons with Firepower 5+ or 6.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8f7c-32a7-f0b9-79d5" name="Flame Tank" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Flame tanks cannont Charge Into Contact and have an Assault rating of 5+.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cc66-d018-683f-fc4a" name="Flame-thrower" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry, Gun and Unarmoured Tank Teams re-roll successful Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower and the Unit is automatically Pinned Down. Armoured Tank Teams use their Top armour for Armour Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower.

Flame-throwers my shoot in Defensive Fire. However, while a Unit that is Hit by a Flame-thrower is Pinned Down, this does not automatically stop the assault. The defender still needs to score five (or eight) hits to stop the assault as normal.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="748e-ec8a-8e9a-dd2a" name="HEAT" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>A Team&apos;s Armour rating is not increased by +1 if it is more than 16&quot;/40cm away when hit by HEAT weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="65be-162c-e711-dd8c" name="Mounted Assault" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>This Team has Assault 4+ and Counterattack 4+ with one Passanger and Assault 3+ and Counterattack 4+ with two or three Passangers. This is shown on the Sd Kfz 251 Transport unit card as an additional motivation and skill column.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="2dc1-2fa9-b015-3fde" name="Panzerfaust - Limited 1" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Each time this Unit shoots, one of its Teams my shoot as a Panzerfaust rather than its usual weapons.

Each time this Unit rolls To Hit in an assault, one of its Teams may attack with a Panzerfaust rather than its usual weapons.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f595-45f0-bab8-a34a" name="Unit Transport" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>The Unit Leader of the Transport Attachment must end the Movement Step within 6&quot;/15cm of the Unit Leader of its Passenger Unit while on the table. If it cannot do this, then the Transport Attachment must be Sent to the Rear (see page 45 of the rulebook).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ac10-45e1-3fee-9357" name="Salvo" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Weapons with a ROF of &apos;SALVO&apos; are Artillery weapons and fire Artillery Bombardments, but use a 10&quot;/25cm square Salvo Template rather than the normal 6&quot;/15cm Artillery Template.

A Salvo Template may not be placed within 6&quot;/15cm of a friendly Team.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3976-9122-0d44-45e0" name="Flying Tank" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Flying Tanks have a worse Is Hit On rating, but a better Save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="df33-e135-9db6-7711" name="Protected Ammo" publicationId="b8e5-51cf-456c-eafb" page="39" hidden="false">
      <description>Tanks with Protected Ammo have a better Remount rating.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
